main event: A bright, green light was observed in the sky over Yellow Springs, Ohio on April 22, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as a bright green light with white trailing edges, moving at a high speed.
The object was observed for about 6 minutes, and was seen to move behind a cloud at one point.
The observer estimated the object was 1-3 miles away and moving at an estimated speed of 105 mph.
The object did not make any sound as it moved and disappeared.
The observer compared the brightness of the object to being brighter than the brightest stars.
